1 AN ACT relating to human growth and development instruction.
2 WHEREAS, the General Assembly recognizes that a comprehensive education on
3 human growth and development is essential to the health, safety, and well-being of
4 Kentucky children; and
5 WHEREAS, age-appropriate instruction ensures that children receive information
6 that is suitable for their developmental stage, protecting their innocence while preparing
7 them for future responsibilities; and
8 WHEREAS, teaching students about human growth and development in a manner
9 aligned with their age promotes understanding of their bodies, relationships, and personal
10 boundaries in a healthy and responsible way; and
11 WHEREAS, parents have the fundamental right to guide the moral and educational
12 upbringing of their children, and curricula should respect and support parental authority;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, schools should ensure that instruction on human growth and
15 development reflects scientifically accurate information, promotes healthy decision
16 making, and prioritizes the safety and long-term welfare of students; and
17 WHEREAS, it is the responsibility of the Commonwealth to provide clear statutory
18 guidance to schools so that instruction promotes public health while upholding family
19 values, parental rights, and developmentally appropriate learning;
20 NOW, THEREFORE,
21 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
22 Section 1. KRS 158.1415 is amended to read as follows:
23 (1) If a school district[ school council or, if none exists, the principal] adopts a
24 curriculum for human sexuality or sexually transmitted diseases, instruction shall
25 include but not be limited to the following content:
26 (a) Abstinence from sexual activity is the desirable goal for all school-age
27 children;
Page 1 of 4
